articles.title: Hybrid solar eclipse on April 20, India to miss out glimpse of the rare eclipse - Times of India
articles.description: A hybrid solar eclipse took place on April 20 lasting about 5 hours and 25 minutes. The eclipse started at 7.04 am and will end at 12.29 pm. This is the first eclipse of 2023. It will be visible in East and South-East Asia, Singapore, Indonesia, Philippines, …
